parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine oil leaks can cause fires, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
Crankshaft pulley failure can cause engine stalling, loss of power, and potential accidents.
Engine stalling and failure can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
Catalytic converter failure can cause engine performance issues, decreased fuel efficiency, and potential environmental hazards.
Harmonic balancer failure can cause engine vibration, noise, and potential engine damage.
Engine cooling system failure can cause engine overheating, damage, and potential accidents.

The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. In some cases, it can also cause fires, which can result in property damage or loss of life.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or won't start
the ignition switch is difficult to turn
the key gets stuck in the ignition
the vehicle runs rough or stalls due to failed distributor cap
